# SONY PSP · SONY PSP · exereunesis · handheld teardown · 2004 · UD0 / exereunesis

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of SONY PSP](the-psp.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (SONY PSP's organic-form embodiment): the-psp.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** SONY PSP — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** Sony brought near-PS2 power to a handheld with a sharp widescreen, a proprietary optical disc, and serious multimedia chops. The PSP was a small powerhouse — its main constraints were the UMD format and a battery that paid for all that performance.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Sony brought near-PS2 power to a handheld with a sharp widescreen, a proprietary optical disc, and serious multimedia chops. The PSP was a small powerhouse — its main constraints were the UMD format and a battery that paid for all that performance.

**how —** Rendered from the public technical record.

**◌ the mythos —** Sony brought near-PS2 power to a handheld with a sharp widescreen, a proprietary optical disc, and serious multimedia chops. The PSP was a small powerhouse — its main constraints were the UMD format and a battery that paid for all that performance. the inside of a made machine, laid bare

